In article <Cv5rCH.MCI@rci.ripco.com>, Robert Zubek <clegg@ripco.com> wrote:
>I'm not sure if this is the right place to ask, but is there any 
>utility/method to crack os/2's lock-up password?  I sure hope there is one 
>(or am I the only one with bad memory?), cause otherwise I'll be bound 
>not to leave my desk for more than few minutes for the rest of my life 
>(or until I reinstall os/2, whichever comes first)...

It's easy to break the OS/2 password.  Just boot from the install diskettes
and go to your root\OS2 directory.  It's documented in your OS/2 manual,
but I believe the command is makeini lock.rc lockini.ini.



